Class NFAGenerator

      • evaluate

        public boolean evaluate(OwnStack<Character> operationStack,
                        OwnStack<NFA> automatonStack)
        Processes the topmost operation of the stack

        Depending on the operation one or more operands are popped off the stack. From them a new NFA is created according to the rules of the popped operation symbol. The created NFA is then pushed onto the NFA stack.

        Parameters:
        operationStack - stack of operations
        automatonStack - stack of operands for the operations
        Returns:
        true if the operation symbol is valid and there are enough operands to be popped. False if a failure is encountered.

      • hasPrecedence

        public boolean hasPrecedence(char operation1,

        Helper method for evaluating the operations in the proper order.
        Parameters:

        operation2 - symbol for compared operation
        Returns:
        true if operation1 has precedence over operation2. Otherwise false.

      • generateNFAFromOneSymbol

        public NFA generateNFAFromOneSymbol(char symbol)
        Creates a simple NFA that recognizes only the input symbol.
        Parameters:
        symbol - Character that the NFA must accept
        Returns:
        NFA that has two states: starting state, and accepting state, which can be reached only by the input symbol.

      • generateNFAFromEmptyString

        public NFA generateNFAFromEmptyString()
        Creates the simplest NFA that accepts only empty string.
        Returns:
        NFA that has its accepting state as starting state. There is only one state in total.
